{"title_page": "Hans Aarsman", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name             = Hans Aarsman\n| image            = Hans Aarsman 2.jpg\n| image_size       =\n| alt              =\n| caption          =\n| birth_name       =\n| birth_date       = {{birth year and age|1951}}\n| birth_place      = [[Amsterdam]], Netherlands\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      =\n| nationality      =\n| known_for        =\n| education        =\n| movement         =\n| notable_works    =\n| patrons          =\n| influenced by    =\n| awards           =\n| elected          =\n| website          = {{url|hansaarsman.nl}}\n}}\n{{commons category|Hans Aarsman}}\n\n'''Hans Aarsman''' (born 1951) is a Dutch photographer, author, and lecturer at the [[Rijksakademie]] in Amsterdam. He is a significant figure in the [[New Topography]] movement.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}} Many of Aarsman's works are in the [[Netherlands Photo Museum]].<ref>[http://www.nederlandsfotomuseum.nl/index.php?option=com_nfm_album&Itemid=183&task=viewer&album_id=10 Netherlands Photo Museum]</ref>\n\n==Life and work==\nAarsman was born in 1951 in [[Amsterdam]]. He started his career as a photojournalist for the Dutch newspaper ''[[Trouw]].'' In 1989 he published the book ''Hollandse Taferelen'' which consisted of [[landscape]]s photographed from the roof of a camper which he pulled through the Netherlands for a year. In 1990\u20131991 he finished a photo series of [[East Germany|East German]] states.\n\nHe exhibited work at the [[Rencontres d'Arles]] festival in Arles, France in 2011.\n\nAarsman also is a novelist and playwright. His debut literary work was ''Twee hoofden, een kussen'' (1995) and more recently he has been dedicating himself more to writing than photography.\n\n==Publications==\n===Photography===\n*''Hollandse Taferelen'' (1989)\n*''Aarsmans Amsterdam'' (1993)\n*''Een engeltje dat over mijn tong piest'' (1995)\n*''Vrrooom! Vrrooom!'' (2003)\n\n===Literature===\n*''Twee hoofden, een kussen'' (1995)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|hansaarsman.nl}}\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7l-I82-Q0y0 Aarsman giving a talk at TEDxAmsterdam in 2009] (video)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aarsman, Hans}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch photographers]]\n[[Category:Writers from Amsterdam]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch male writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Dutch male novelists]]\n[[Category:Dutch male dramatists and playwrights]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-artist-stub}}\n{{Europe-photographer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name             = Hans Aarsman\n| image            = Hans Aarsman 2.jpg\n| image_size       =\n| alt              =\n| caption          =\n| birth_name       =\n| birth_date       = {{birth year and age|1951}}\n| birth_place      = [[Amsterdam]], Netherlands\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      =\n| nationality      =\n| known_for        =\n| education        =\n| movement         =\n| notable_works    =\n| patrons          =\n| influenced by    =\n| awards           =\n| elected          =\n| website          = {{url|hansaarsman.nl}}\n}}\n{{commons category|Hans Aarsman}}\n\n'''Hans Aarsman''' (born 1951) is a Dutch photographer, author, and lecturer at the [[Rijksakademie]] in Amsterdam. He is a significant figure in the [[New Topography]] movement.{{citation needed|date=April 2017}} Many of Aarsman's works are in the [[Netherlands Photo Museum]].<ref>[http://www.nederlandsfotomuseum.nl/index.php?option=com_nfm_album&Itemid=183&task=viewer&album_id=10 Netherlands Photo Museum]</ref>\n\n==Life and work==\nAarsman was born in 1951 in [[Amsterdam]]. He started his career as a photojournalist for the Dutch newspaper ''[[Trouw]].'' In 1989 he published the book ''Hollandse Taferelen'' which consisted of [[landscape]]s photographed from the roof of a camper which he pulled through the Netherlands for a year. In 1990\u20131991 he finished a photo series of [[East Germany|East German]] states.\n\nHe exhibited work at the [[Rencontres d'Arles]] festival in Arles, France in 2011.\n\nAarsman also is a novelist and playwright. His debut literary work was ''Twee hoofden, een kussen'' (1995) and more recently he has been dedicating himself more to writing than photography.\n\n==Publications==\n===Photography===\n*''Hollandse Taferelen'' (1989)\n*''Aarsmans Amsterdam'' (1993)\n*''Een engeltje dat over mijn tong piest'' (1995)\n*''Vrrooom! Vrrooom!'' (2003)\n\n===Literature===\n*''Twee hoofden, een kussen'' (1995)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|hansaarsman.nl}}\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7l-I82-Q0y0 Aarsman giving a talk at TEDxAmsterdam in 2009] (video)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aarsman, Hans}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dutch photographers]]\n[[Category:Writers from Amsterdam]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch novelists]]\n[[Category:Dutch male novelists]]\n[[Category:Dutch dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Male dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch male writers]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-artist-stub}}\n{{Europe-photographer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:recat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Aarsman"}
{"title_page": "Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez", "text_new": "{{for|the Mexican cyclist|Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez (cyclist)}}\n{{Spanish name|Guti\u00e9rrez|Ar\u00e9valo}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n| name = Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez\n| image = Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez.jpg\n| caption = Guti\u00e9rrez in 2015\n| birth_name = Ariadna Mar\u00eda Guti\u00e9rrez Ar\u00e9valo\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|12|25|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Sincelejo]], [[Colombia]]\n| hometown = [[Barranquilla]], [[Colombia]]\n| residence = [[Miami]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| height = \n| years_active = 2015\u2013present\n| hair_color = Auburn\n| eye_color = Brown\n| title = [[Miss Colombia 2014]]\n| nationalcompetition = [[Miss Colombia 2014]]<br>(Winner)<br>[[Miss Universe 2015]]<br>(1st Runner-Up)\n}}\n\n'''Ariadna Mar\u00eda Guti\u00e9rrez Ar\u00e9valo''' (born December 25, 1993) is a Colombian model, actress, and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned [[Miss Colombia 2014]]. Guti\u00e9rrez placed as the first runner-up in [[Miss Universe 2015]], where she was mistakenly announced as the winner by host [[Steve Harvey]]. After pageantry, she starred in the film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]'' and was a finalist on ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 1 (U.S.)|Celebrity Big Brother 1]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nGuti\u00e9rrez was born in [[Sincelejo]], Colombia. When she was seven months old, her parents moved to [[Barranquilla]], where she was raised. She studied at the German School of Barranquilla.<ref>{{cite web|title = Senorita Colombia 2014|url = http://www.sucre.gov.co/noticias.shtml?apc=ccx-1-&x=1531004|website = sucre.gov.co|language = Spanish|access-date = 2014-12-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170311161434/http://www.sucre.gov.co/noticias.shtml?apc=ccx-1-&x=1531004|archive-date = 2017-03-11|url-status = dead}} Retrieved in 2014.</ref> She is a cousin of [[Miss Universe 2014]] and [[Miss Colombia 2013]] winner [[Paulina Vega]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.today.com/video/miss-colombia-my-cousin-removed-my-crown-during-botched-ceremony-605119043503|title=Miss Colombia: My cousin removed my crown during botched ceremony|publisher=Today|date=20 January 2016}}</ref> Guti\u00e9rrez is fluent in Spanish, English and German.{{Citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Career==\nGuti\u00e9rrez was awarded as Se\u00f1orita Sucre (Miss Sucre Colombia 2014). She was subsequently crowned as [[Miss Colombia 2014]]. Currently she is working as a professional model.{{Citation needed|date=February 2016}}\n\nGuti\u00e9rrez competed at the [[Miss Colombia 2014]], representing the [[Sucre Department]], where she won the title of Miss Colombia, gaining the department's very first win at the [[Miss Colombia]] pageant.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}} The version of the pageant she won was its 80th edition held on November 17, 2014, in [[Cartagena de Indias]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ariadna Gutierrez de Sucre Nueva Senorita Colombia 2014|url=http://vidayestilo.terra.com/mujer/belleza/ariadna-gutierrez-de-sucre-nueva-senorita-colombia,06c3e643740c9410VgnCLD200000b1bf46d0RCRD.html|website=vidayestilo.tierra.com}} Retrieved in 2014.</ref>\n\nOn November 16, 2015, Gutierrez crowned her successor, [[Andrea Tovar]], as [[Miss Colombia 2015]].\n\nGuti\u00e9rrez represented [[Colombia]] at the 2015 [[Miss Universe]] pageant. Initially, host [[Steve Harvey]] announced Guti\u00e9rrez as Miss Universe 2015 and Miss Philippines, [[Pia Wurtzbach]], as the first runner-up.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Wrong contestant crowned at Miss Universe 2015|url = http://www.cnn.com/2015/12/20/us/miss-universe-wrong-contestant-crowned/index.html|website = CNN|accessdate = 21 December 2015|date = 21 December 2015}}</ref> However, after Guti\u00e9rrez's crowning, Harvey realized that he had misread the result and should have announced Colombia as the first runner-up<ref>{{cite news |last = Pierceall|first = Kimberly|date = 21 December 2015|title = Miss Universe host's mistake initially gives crown to Colombia, not Philippines|url = https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/miss-universe-hosts-mistake-initially-gives-crown-to-colombia-not-philippines/article27891455/|newspaper = Globe and Mail|location = Toronto, Canada|access-date = 30 December 2015}}</ref> and that Wurtzbach was Miss Universe. Harvey then amended his previous announcement while the current Miss Universe also from [[Colombia]], [[Paulina Vega]], transferred the DIC crown over to Wurtzbach as the televised broadcast abruptly ended.\n\nGuti\u00e9rrez later called the experience \"humiliating\" and declared that the television producers handled the mistake poorly. At a Colombian radio station, she remarked that it was a \"great injustice and very humiliating for me.\"<ref>[http://www.stuff.co.nz/life-style/beauty/75582803/miss-colombia-ariadna-gutierrez-speaks-out-about-humiliating-miss-universe-mixup Miss Colombia Ariadna Gutierrez speaks out about 'humiliating' Miss Universe mix-up.]</ref><ref>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/miss-colombia-calls-miss-universe-851615 Miss Colombia Talks \"Humiliating\" Miss Universe Mix-Up, Why She Agrees With Trump.]</ref>\n\nAfter pageantry, Guti\u00e9rrez starred the 2017 film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]'' with American actor [[Vin Diesel]]. Guti\u00e9rrez later took part in the [[Celebrity Big Brother 1 (U.S.)|first American season]] of the reality show competition ''[[Celebrity Big Brother (U.S. TV series)|Celebrity Big Brother]]''. She was evicted on finale night, placing tied 3rd/4th with [[Mark McGrath]].<ref>[http://www.cbs.com/shows/celebrity-big-brother/cast/215850 Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez]</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGuti\u00e9rrez resides in [[Miami]], [[Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbs.com/shows/celebrity-big-brother/photos/1008130/meet-the-famous-cast-of-celebrity-big-brother/127304/ariadna-guti-rrez/|title=Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez Biography|accessdate=29 January 2018|publisher=CBS}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Primer Plano''\n| Herself\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Steve Harvey (TV series)|Steve Harvey]]''\n| Herself\n| Miss Universe Colombia 2015\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 1 (U.S.)|Celebrity Big Brother]]''\n| Herself\n| Houseguest - 3rd/4th place<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/television/8099559/celebrity-big-brother-cast-pics-bios |title=Get to Know the 'Celebrity Big Brother' Cast: Mark McGrath, Omarosa & More |last=Maher |first=Natalie |date=February 13, 2018 |website=www.billboard.com |access-date=February 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The World's Best]]''\n| Herself\n|\n|}\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]''\n| Gina Roff\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! width=\"42\" | Year\n! width=\"250\" | Artist\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Title\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[Carlos Vives]]<ref name=\"eonline.com\">{{cite web|title=Carlos Vives Premieres Music Video for \"Al Filo de Tu Amor\" Featuring Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/823827/carlos-vives-premieres-music-video-for-al-filo-de-tu-amor-featuring-ariadna-gutierrez|website=eonline.com|accessdate=23 January 2017}}</ref>\n| [[Carlos Vives discography|Al Filo de Tu Amor]]<ref name=\"eonline.com\" />\n|}\n\n==In popular culture==\nAriadna Guti\u00e9rrez was impersonated by James Leyva, stage name \"[[Valentina (drag queen)|Valentina]],\" on season 9, episode 6 of ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 9)|RuPaul's Drag Race]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.srtacolombia.org/ Official Miss Colombia website]\n* {{IMDb name|7803367}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{S-bef|before={{flagicon|USA}} [[Nia Sanchez]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Miss Universe]] 1st Runner-Up\n|years=[[Miss Universe 2015|2015]]}}\n{{S-aft|after={{flagicon|Haiti}} [[Raquel P\u00e9lissier]]}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[File:Flag of Atl\u00e1ntico.svg|border|22x20px|Atl\u00e1ntico]] [[Paulina Vega]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Miss Colombia]]\n|years=2014}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[File:Flag of Choc\u00f3.svg|border|22x20px|Choc\u00f3]] [[Andrea Tovar]]}}\n{{S-bef|before=Andrea Pe\u00f1uela}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Sucre Department|Miss Sucre]]\n|years=2014}}\n{{S-aft|after=Paula Correa}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Miss Universe 2015 delegates}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gutierrez, Ariadna}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Colombian actresses]]\n[[Category:Colombian beauty pageant winners]]\n[[Category:Colombian expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Colombian female models]]\n[[Category:Colombian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Miss Colombia winners]]\n[[Category:Miss Universe 2015 contestants]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Barranquilla]]\n[[Category:People from Sincelejo]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Mexican cyclist|Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez (cyclist)}}\n{{Spanish name|Guti\u00e9rrez|Ar\u00e9valo}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n| name = Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez\n| image = Ariadna Guti\u00e9rrez.jpg\n| caption = Guti\u00e9rrez in 2015\n| birth_name = Ariadna Mar\u00eda Guti\u00e9rrez Ar\u00e9valo\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|12|25|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Sincelejo]], [[Colombia]]\n| hometown = [[Barranquilla]], [[Colombia]]\n| residence = [[Miami]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| height = \n| years_active = 2015\u2013present\n| hair_color = Auburn\n| eye_color = Brown\n| title = [[Miss Colombia 2014]]\n| nationalcompetition = [[Miss Colombia 2014]]<br>(Winner)<br>[[Miss Universe 2015]]<br>(1st Runner-Up)\n}}\n\n'''Ariadna Mar\u00eda Guti\u00e9rrez Ar\u00e9valo''' (born December 25, 1993) is a Colombian model, actress, and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned [[Miss Colombia 2014]]. Guti\u00e9rrez placed as the first runner-up in [[Miss Universe 2015]], where she was mistakenly announced as the winner by host [[Steve Harvey]]. After pageantry, she starred in the film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]'' and was a finalist on ''[[Celebrity Big Brother 1 (U.S.)|Celebrity Big Brother 1]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nGuti\u00e9rrez was born in [[Sincelejo]], Colombia. When she was seven months old, her parents moved to [[Barranquilla]], where she was raised. She studied at the German School of Barranquilla.<ref>{{cite web|title = Senorita Colombia 2014|url = http://www.sucre.gov.co/noticias.shtml?apc=ccx-1-&x=1531004|website = sucre.gov.co|language = Spanish|access-date = 2014-12-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170311161434/http://www.sucre.gov.co/noticias.shtml?apc=ccx-1-&x=1531004|archive-date = 2017-03-11|url-status = dead}} Retrieved in 2014.</ref> She is a cousin of [[Miss Universe 2014]] and [[Miss Colombia 2013]] winner [[Paulina Vega]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.today.com/video/miss-colombia-my-cousin-removed-my-crown-during-botched-ceremony-605119043503|title=Miss Colombia: My cousin removed my crown during botched ceremony|publisher=Today|date=20 January 2016}}</ref> Guti\u00e9rrez is fluent in Spanish, English and German.{{Citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Career==\nGuti\u00e9rrez was awarded as Se\u00f1orita Sucre (Miss Sucre Colombia 2014). She was subsequently crowned as [[Miss Colombia 2014]]. Currently she is working as a professional model.{{Citation needed|date=February 2016}}\n\nGuti\u00e9rrez competed at the [[Miss Colombia 2014]], representing the [[Sucre Department]], where she won the title of Miss Colombia, gaining the department's very first win at the [[Miss Colombia]] pageant.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}} The version of the pageant she won was its 80th edition held on November 17, 2014, in [[Cartagena de Indias]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ariadna Gutierrez de Sucre Nueva Senorita Colombia 2014|url=http://vidayestilo.terra.com/