ood]]\n  |votes      = 25,440\n  |percentage = 42.4\n  |change     = {{decrease}}3.3\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Marie Tidball\n  |votes      = 7,573\n  |percentage = 12.6\n  |change     = {{decrease}}0.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link |\n  |party      = UK Independence Party\n  |candidate  = Alan Harris\n  |votes      = 751\n  |percentage = 1.3\n  |change     = {{decrease}}5.7\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 816\n  |percentage = 1.4\n  |change     = {{increase}} 18.1\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = 60,020\n  |percentage = 79.6\n  |change     = {{increase}} 4.4\n}}\n{{Election box gain with party link|\n  |winner     = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n  |loser      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |swing      = {{increase}} 9.1\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{see also|Opinion polling in United Kingdom constituencies, 2010\u201315#Oxford West and Abingdon}}\n{{Election box begin | title=[[2015 United Kingdom general election|General election 2015]]: Oxford West and Abingdon<ref name=electoralcalculus>{{cite web|title=Election Data 2015|url=http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2015.txt|publisher=[[Electoral Calculus]]|accessdate=17 October 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151017112223/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2015.txt|archivedate=17 October 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Nicola Blackwood]]\n  |votes      = 26,153\n  |percentage = 45.7\n  |change     = {{increase}} 3.4\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link |\n  |party      = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Layla Moran]]\n  |votes      = 16,571\n  |percentage = 28.9\n  |change     = {{decrease}} 13.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link |\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Sally Copley\n  |votes      = 7,274\n  |percentage = 12.7\n  |change  