chive.org/web/20111015054424/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_1997.txt|archivedate=15 October 2011}}</ref><ref>C. Rallings & M. Thrasher, The Media Guide to the New Parliamentary Constituencies, p.451 (Plymouth: LGC Elections Centre, 1995)</ref><ref>The 1997 election result is calculated relative to the notional, not the actual, 1992 result.</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n  |candidate  = [[Evan Harris]]\n  |votes      = 26,268\n  |percentage = 42.9\n  |change     = +7.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Laurence Harris\n  |votes      = 19,983\n  |percentage = 32.7\n  |change     = \u221213.6\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Susan Brown\n  |votes      = 12,361\n  |percentage = 20.2\n  |change     = +4.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Referendum Party\n  |candidate  = Gillian Eustace\n  |votes      = 1,258\n  |percentage = 2.1\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Green Party of England and Wales\n  |candidate  = [[Mike Woodin]]\n  |votes      = 691\n  |percentage = 1.1\n  |change     = \u22120.1\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = UK Independence Party\n  |candidate  = Rodney Buckton\n  |votes      = 258\n  |percentage = 0.4\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = ProLife Alliance\n  |candidate  = Linda Hodge\n  |votes      = 238\n  |percentage = 0.4\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Natural Law Party\n  |candidate  = Anne Wilson\n  |votes      = 91\n  |percentage = 0.1\n  |change     = +0.0\n}}\n{{Election box candidate|\n  |party      = Local Government\n  |candidate  = John Rose\n  |votes      = 48\n  |percentage = 0.1\n  |change     = ''